<SLUG> BC-CASH-CARD-BONUS-NYT </SLUG>
  
 SMART CARD COMES WITH A BURGER BONUS  (lh) 
 
 By PETER WAYNER   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ For several years, Mastercard International's Mondex
unit has been trying to get Americans to use its smart card rather
than cash for small transactions. Now the same folks are offering
free food as the incentive.
</P>
<P>
   The company is conducting a test with Burger King that offers
bonus points, redeemable for Whoppers and the like, to customers
who use Mondex's card system at four Burger King restaurants on
Long Island.
</P>
<P>
   The Mondex card is embedded with a special chip that keeps track
of purchases. A $10 card buys $10 worth of food, but for every
dollar customers spend they receive one loyalty point. Ten points
can be redeemed for a breakfast meal and 15 for a Whopper sandwich.
</P>
<P>
   The Mondex trial, which began in June and runs through December,
is not the only high-technology promotion the fast-food chain is
offering. Last month, a Burger King restaurant in Manhattan started
offering free Internet access from 20 PC's. Customers receive 20
free minutes on line when they spend a minimum of $4.99.
</P>
<P>
   The stores are also installing card readers in drive-through
lanes, where Mondex thinks the cards will be particularly popular,
saving drivers from digging into their pockets for cash.
</P>
</TEXT>
