three-week-old civil war are redrawn as government soldiers and
their allies recapture a critical military base near the Atlantic
coast, greatly reducing the possibility that rebel forces could
march into the capital here. By Norimitsu Onishi. (With map.)
</P>
<P>
   ATTACK-AFGHAN-TERRAIN (Washington) _ Afghanistan has a long
history of repelling superpowers; its terrain favors defenders as
well as any in the world. It is uncertain that the United States,
which fired dozens of cruise missiles at those same camps on
Thursday, can do better than the Soviets. By Tim Weiner. (With
map.)
</P>
