plane crashes, Mau Mau marauders and domestic life on safari with
his fourth wife, Mary, Ernest Hemingway returned home to Cuba and
began work on a long autobiographical novel. ``This is it; there
are no more books,'' said Charles Scribner III, whose family
imprint, now part of Simon &AMP; Schuster, is bringing out what it
calls the fictional memoir, ``True at First Light,'' as edited by
Hemingway's 70-year-old middle son, Patrick. By Ralph Blumenthal.
