<SLUG> BC-AUSTIN-WARNER25-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   CNN-style channel planned for Austin
</P>
<P>
   By R. Michelle Breyer
</P>
<P>
   Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Time Warner Cable will launch a local all-news,
24-hour television channel next spring _ a CNN-style station for
Austin.
</P>
<P>
   The channel will be available to more than 220,000 of the cable
company's subscribers in areas where the company has installed
fiber-optic cable _ including Austin, Round Rock, Leander and West
Lake Hills. It will report on local news, sports, weather and
special features from Austin and Central Texas, operating from a
20,000-square-foot studio that will be built at 16th and Colorado
streets. Time Warner will most likely change the format of an
existing television channel for the news channel, officials said.
</P>
<P>
   Time Warner, the nation's second-largest cable television
operator, has launched similar channels in New York City and
Rochester in New York and Orlando and the Tampa Bay area in
Florida.
</P>
<P>
   Nationwide, there are more than two dozen local 24-hour cable
news channels operated by Time Warner and other companies.
Elsewhere in Texas, A.H. Belo Corp., which owns the Dallas Morning
News, also plans to start a cable news channel next year.
</P>
<P>
   The news channel in Austin will be Time Warner's first in a
smaller market. The others have been in the nation's 20 biggest
markets.
</P>
<P>
   ``Austin was chosen because it is a very vibrant, growing
area,'' said Bill Carey, president of the Austin division of Time
Warner. ``I personally believe the time is right for this type of
programming here in Austin.''
</P>
<P>
   In New York City, where the concept was started six years ago,
the channel is called NY1. In the Tampa Bay area, it's Bay News 9,
and in Orlando, it's Central Florida News 13. No name has been
selected for the Austin station.
</P>
<P>
   Time Warner plans to hire 60 to 70 reporters, editors, video
journalists, producers and anchors for the new Austin channel. In
other markets, like Orlando, it has teamed up with local newspapers
to provide coverage. At this time, the company said it has no
formal agreements with any local news organization in Austin.
</P>
<P>
   The entire focus of the channel will be Central Texas news _ ``a
local version that will operate like CNN's Headline News,'' Carey
said.
</P>
<P>
   In the Tampa Bay area, viewers see a repeating cycle of
broadcasts that are divided into half-hour packages of stories,
which can be modified as the day progresses. The station features
weather reports every nine minutes, and a half-hour sports call-in
show.
</P>
<P>
   Time Warner Cable is part of Time Warner Inc., one of the
nation's largest media conglomerates. It has 243,000 customers in
the Austin and Central Texas area.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
