<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ I was convinced it was my love, affection, and
dedication that had brought my son this far. But that was last
week. This week all the talk is about a book written by a New
Jersey grandmother who claims parents have little or nothing to do
with their children's successes or failures. (Schuett, Cox News
Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   GEEWAX-COLUMN _ ATLANTA _ When he spoke on the Monica Lewinsky
matter last week, President Clinton insisted that his private life
should remain private. Unfortunately, what the president did behind
closed doors with a former White House intern does directly involve
all of us and our wallets. (Geewax, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
(k, f)
</P>
<P>
   MURRAY-COLUMN _ This was my seventh trip to Russia. Lucky seven.
With any luck, I'm never coming back. (Murray, Lufkin Daily News)
MOVED 8/21.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ One reason I avidly read every word I could
about the Barnicle saga is that I constantly steal jokes, puns and
one-liners for columns. If you read a joke or pun in my column, the
odds are overwhelming that I stole it. There, I said it. (Borders,
Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   MINOR-COLUMN _ This is crazy, I know. It's been more than four
months since I smoked my last cigarette. Four months. Most days are
easy, most days just whiz by. But sometimes, out of nowhere, comes
an urge so powerful, so compelling, so mind-controlling, that I am
frozen right then and there. (Minor, Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
