   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   RICHARDSON-ENERGY (Washington) _ Bill Richardson, the new Energy
Department secretary, pledges to catch up with other nations in
decreasing pollutants. In an address to the department's employees,
the former United Nations envoy says the United States needs commit
itself to solar power and other renewable energy sources. By NICOLE
TSONG.
</P>
