346-9867. And be sure to look for other entertainment stories from
our partners: Bloomberg News, The Boston Globe, Cox News Service,
Hearst Newspapers, The Houston Chronicle, The Arizona Republic,
Kansas City Star, Fort Worth Star-Telegram, Los Angeles Daily News,
San Francisco Chronicle and Seattle Post-Intelligencer.
</P>
<P>
   MARRAKESH, Morocco _ Not long ago the imam at the Casbah mosque
agreed to show me his ancient minbar _ Minbars are decorated wooden
staircases on wheels from which the imam addresses the congregation
during Friday worship. The idea was to compare it to the
12th-century minbar from the Kutubiyya mosque here, which
conservators from the Metropolitan Museum of Art have lately
restored and installed to justified local fanfare, in the remains
of the city's immense Badi Palace. The smaller Casbah minbar is
great, too _ though a wreck _ and is still in use. So however they
compare esthetically, the two minbars have now become fundamentally
different kinds of objects and reflect different approaches to
treasured objects from the past. By Michael Kimmelman.
</P>
<P>
   LUCERNE-MUSIC-FEST (Lucerne, Switzerland) _ Arts Abroad: The
International Music Festival in Lucerne. By Alan Riding.
</P>
