<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; RUSSIA TURMOIL &LR;  (``i'' code)
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times plans this package of stories covering the
economic and political turmoil in Russia.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; RUSSIA &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-SHAKEUP (Moscow) _ Ledeall on the Russia
government/financial upheaval. By Michael R. Gordon.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-VOICES (Moscow) _ Reaction around the capital. By Michael
Wines.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-POWER (Moscow) _ Who are the oligarchs behind the throne?
By Celestine Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-U.S. (Washington) _ The United States has tried to tread
carefully in the days leading up to the summit conference, as it
closely monitors developments in Russia. By Steven Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-GERMANY (Bonn) _ Germany, Russia's biggest foreign
investor, responds to the Russian crisis. By Edmund L. Andrews.
</P>
