   Nor is sending the police to warn him off likely to do any good,
de Becker says. Unless the pursuer has committed a crime that
warrants his arrest, the police can do little more than talk, which
may further embolden the stalker.
</P>
<P>
   Even obtaining a restraining order can sometimes backfire. Court
