<HEADLINE>
SHOCK COLLAR CAUTIONS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By THOMAS ROPP  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - Study all instructional booklets and instructional
videos before using a shock collar.
</P>
<P>
   - Buy a collar with adjustable shock levels and always start
with the lowest level.
</P>
<P>
   -Before installing batteries, allow your dog to wear the unarmed
collar for a few days so he doesn't associate the correction with
the equipment.
</P>
<P>
   - Remove the collar between training sessions.
</P>
<P>
   - Never allow children access to the transmitter.
</P>
<P>
   - Use the collar as an adjunct to more traditional obedience
training. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Source: Radio Fence Distributors &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
