Clinton's censure or resignation, Vice President Al Gore remains
fiercely loyal to his mentor, counting on his own clean personal
life to distance himself from the Monica Lewinsky affair. Actually,
Gore has little choice but to stand by Clinton; any change in their
partnership now would be seen as a betrayal not likely to sit well
with voters. By MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
