<P>
   PANAM-TRIAL (Washington) -- Secretary of State Madeleine
Albright informs families of the Lockerbie plane explosion victims
of a new US-Britain proposal to try two Libyan suspects in a
Scottish court convened in The Hague. By Bob Hohler. 1200 words. (i
and a coding)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   CLINTONS-VINEYARD (Edgartown, Mass.) -- The Clintons lunch
separately with friends _ he with Vernon Jordan, she at a boat
party with female friends. By Brian McGrory.
</P>
<P>
   MOB-HEARING (Boston) -- Confronted repeatedly with the FBI's
paper trail of his years informing on the Mafia, Stephen ``The
Rifleman'' Flemmi has a ready response: He takes the Fifth. By
Patricia Nealon. 800 words.
</P>
