the SEC for negligent conduct, Merrill Lynch agrees to pay a $2
million civil fine to settle allegations it misled investors when
it underwrote Orange County municipal securities months before the
county's disastrous bankruptcy. By Lynnley Browning. 600 words.
</P>
<P>
   PAGING-INTERACTIVE (Undated) -- BellSouth Wireless Data is about
to launch interactive paging service in 10 cities that would allow
users to send and receive e-mail, not just pages. By Joann Muller.
800 words.
</P>
