</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Elton John pops up in different settings
 &HT;    By Russ DeVault
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Look closely, and there's something for Elton John fans of
almost any age available or coming to market. For starters, there's
the lightly publicized compilation of others' tunes that he
recorded early in his career, ``16 Legendary Covers From 1969/70.''
It includes versions of ``Up Around the Bend,'' ``Love of the
Common People'' and ``Spirit in the Sky.''
</P>
<P>
   In addition, John can be heard singing ``Stand by Your Man'' on
the Asylum tribute album ``Tammy Wynette Remembered'' when it
arrives at retail stores Sept. 8. Also due that day is ``Disney's
Greatest Pop Hits,'' which includes ``Can You Feel the Love
Tonight'' and ``Circle of Life.''
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Dance With Me _ Music From the Motion Picture'' soundtrack
(Epic). Review in Thursday Living. Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Disney's Greatest Pop Hits'' compilation.
</P>
<P>
   -- Lauryn Hill, ``The Miseducation of Lauryn Hill'' (Columbia).
Grade: A.
</P>
<P>
   -- Hootie &AMP; the Blowfish, ``Musical Chairs'' (Atlantic). Due
Sept. 15.
</P>
<P>
   -- Elton John, ``16 Legendary Covers From 1969/70'' (Purple
Pyramid). Grade: B.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Slums of Beverly Hills'' soundtrack (BMG). Mostly '60s
stars do classics.
</P>
<P>
   -- The Temptations, ``Phoenix Rising'' (Motown). Sole remaining
original is tenor Otis Williams.
</P>
<P>
   -- ``Tammy Wynette Remembered'' compilation (Asylum).
</P>
