A9862 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBN-FALCONS25-COX     08-24 0533
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-FALCONS25-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Not many surprises as Falcons go to 60
 &HT;    By Matt Winkeljohn
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ The Atlanta Falcons cut their roster from 78 to 62
players Monday, and will waive two more players today to meet the
NFL's 60-man roster limit.
</P>
<P>
   There were few surprises. Atlanta cut three offensive linemen,
four wide receivers, three defensive linemen, three defensive
backs, a fullback, a kicker and rookie quarterback John Dutton.
</P>
<P>
   The NFL's final cutdown is Sunday, when rosters must be reduced
to 53.
</P>
<P>
   Former University of Georgia lineman Scott Adams, an eight-year
veteran who has spent time with nine different teams, was the most
experienced player cut. Third-year wide receiver Mercury Hayes,
picked up last year after being waived by New Orleans, also got
cut.
</P>
<P>
   Six of the 16 players were rookies, and another five had one
year of experience, either on Atlanta's practice squad or in a
training camp last year.
</P>
<P>
   Henry Slay, a 6-foot-1, 290-pound seventh-round pick from West
Virginia, was the only 1998 draft pick cut. The Falcons drafted
nine players during the April draft.
</P>
<P>
   Backup free safety Marcus Wimberly, the Falcons' fifth-round
choice last year, was waived, moving rookie fourth-rounder Omar
Brown into a backup spot behind Eugene Robinson.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not a fun day for a coach,'' Falcons coach Dan Reeves
said. ``It's probably the worst day of the year. We had some tough
decisions to make, which is nice. We just think we got some people
that were playing a little bit better, guys with a little more
upside (potential).''
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons waived fifth-year defensive tackle Williams Gaines
(knee/back) and defensive end Barry Mitchell (elbow/quad) after
reaching injury settlements with them. Mitchell, who was on the
team's practice squad last year, missed 21 practices with
quadriceps and elbow injuries.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just couldn't come back (from injury) fast enough,''
Mitchell said. ``I'd give back everything in this envelope (with
his settlement) to practice (today).''
</P>
<P>
   The Falcons have three quarterbacks (Chris Chandler, Tony
Graziani, and Steve DeBerg) and four defensive tackles (Travis
Hall, Shane Dronett, Esera Tuaolo and Shawn Swayda) and probably
will keep those numbers.
</P>
<P>
   But Reeves said that doesn't mean the faces won't change. Team
officials were searching the waiver wire on Monday.
</P>
<P>
