   DRUG-STRATEGY (Washington) _ The Clinton administration's drug
policy director will propose changes in the nation's strategy to
stem narcotics trafficking that includes naming a federal
coordinator for all entry ports along the U.S.-Mexico border.
Retired Army Gen. Barry McCaffrey says a ``coherent, coordinated''
effort is needed to stop drugs from entering the country. By GARY
MARTIN. (Already filed)
