Russia's prime minister in a more powerful personal position than
he was before President Boris Yeltsin fired him five months ago. In
the midst of a financial crisis, Yeltsin ``humiliated himself'' by
recalling the man he fired in a Cabinet shuffle, one analyst says.
By BERNARD D. KAPLAN. (Already filed)
