<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, AUGUST 25
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-CLINTON-NOTEBOOK-NYT (moved on Saturday, August 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, August
22, about President Clinton's vacation on Martha's Vineyard
referred incompletely in some copies to the host of the private
party he attended on Saturday night. In addition to being chairman
of WNET public television in New York, Steven Rattner is deputy
chief executive of Lazard Freres &AMP; Company and a major campaign
contributor to the Democrats.
</P>
<P>
   BC-MEDIA-TALK-NYT (moved on Sunday, August 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, August 23,
about fallout from the resignation of the columnist Mike Barnicle
from The Boston Globe misspelled the surname of the media critic
for the on-line magazine Slate. He is Scott Shuger, not Shugar.
</P>
</TEXT>
